---
/* Coda for "How the Night Glows": the hotel window over night-time Shinjuku.
   The city waits in grey behind the glass. Three strikes, like in the story —
   the first leaves a mark, the second webs the glass and opens a hole at the
   point of impact, the third smashes the pane until only a jagged perimeter
   remains, and only then does the city bloom into colour. All glass effects
   are pixel art, in keeping with the site's other codas. Same on all
   viewports; it lives at the end of the story, a classic bottom coda. */
import tokyoGif from '../assets/codas/tokyo-night.gif?url';
import { assetPath } from '../lib/paths';
---

